description: Expatriate Japanese artist Benkei lives in New York. His secret? He may be the only artist in town who isn't entertaining fantasies of being a hitman -- he's living them.

deck: When the team comes up with a plan to hide the death of Captain Zero from the police, Rhapsody does not handle it well and unleashes the full force of her power on her own teammates!
description:
Summit City's most beloved hero, Captain Zero, is murdered in his home. The local authorities want answers, but Captain Zero's fellow heroes must protect his secret identity to preserve their own. Can they solve the mystery without losing everything?

After returning from a long night of questioning from the local authorities, the team arrives back at headquarters to find Major Impact hatching a plan to cover up the disappearance of Captain Zero. Rhapsody does not approve, and lashes out at her teammates with her powers. After all is settled, Insight spends some time with a member of the Zero Technologies staff to discuss how to proceed going forward without Captain Zero.

description:
Along with your usual smattering of brain munching goblins, boneheaded barbarians and delusional psychiatric patients, Issue 7 of the 100% Biodegradable anthology features a new ongoing series - Death Duty, by John Freeman (Dr Who Magazine, Judge Dredd Megazine, Crucible) and Alan Burrows (2000ad, Starblazer, Commando).

'In a war-torn future, crime and disloyalty to the Terran Empire are punished with conscription into mercenary law enforcement squads: soldiers consigned to do or die in order to prove their commitment to the common good. The average life expectancy for a recruit is four months, hence the street slang for the job: Death Duty.

Dissidents in the Terran Empire are put on the infamous "List" - tracked down by Death Duty squads and terminated for their rebellion with extreme prejudice. For most of the Dutymen, exactly who they kill doesn't matter - until one of their number, Travis Wilson, begins to question the missions they're assigned and goes AWOL - a wanted man.

76 pages of Earth's Mightiest Heroes!

The Black Widow's dark past catches up with her in Russia! By Kelly Sue DeConnick, Pete Woods and Mark Bagley!

Rogue attacks the Scarlet Witch! The Apocalypse Twins' scheme reaches its climax! Are the Uncanny Avengers doomed?! Don't miss a shocking story from Rick Remender and Steve McNiven!

Loki is beside himself as the forces of the Mother Parasite assault the Young Avengers! More cutting-edge crazy from Kieron Gillen and Jamie McKelvie!

Featuring material first printed in Uncanny Avengers #14, Avengers Assemble #13 and Young Avengers #5.
Two coffins containing the bodies of Batman and Robin are delivered to Bruce Wayne and Dick Grayson. When they suddenly become animated, they convey a dire prediction.
name: Mystery of the Outsider Part 2 of 4

description:
Has Walter finally found a way to defeat Dennis once and for all? Find out in the ultimate showdown... Walter vs. Dennis! The future of fun in Beanotown is at stake!

What else is happening this week?

  • Will Billy Whizz be saved by the bell?
  • Make Frankenworms!
  • Unravel the meatball mayhem!

PLUS... get your mitts on a free mag! Use the exclusive coupon in exchange for a copy of 110% Gaming! What are you waiting for?

Join Dennis and Gnasher and their new pal, Trunky the Menace, in their escape from Beanotown Zoo!

Also in Beanotown this week...

  • Those food-gobbling pests, the Nibblers are back!
  • Go LOOpy with our toilet roll ninjas!
  • Awesome Pokemon and LEGO Ninjago prizes to win!

PLUS... 23 LOL comics and all-new Menace missions!

Its been several months since the events of The Yellow M, but the evil of Professor Septimus still echoes around London. Important figures of the capitals jet set come together around the questionable values the mad scientist defended. Olrik is forced to resort to opium in order to forget he was guinea pig. As for Mortimer, he too is trying, albeit for more humanist reasons, to revive certain aspects of Septimuss work to Blakes extreme concern
name: The Septimus Wave

description: Our story continues as we learn more about our hero and his past...

Kalast Bridge Takedown

As a result of Blood Forces murdering an Impact Terra delivery driver a new player moves onto the board - enter arms dealer Kerry Passan.
name: Kalast Bridge Takedown

description:
Dragon Slayer follows three characters as they seek revenge. El Diel, an outsider to the bustling feudal metropolis of Bel Brixus, sets out to kill the king who has provoked the destruction of his kingdom at the hands of a dragon. In the wake of Bel Brixus' destruction, King Aldebrand seeks to kill the dragon alone and unaided, leaving his army in shambles and the population to nurse its wounds.

His city is smoldering, and with his kingdom still in ruins, he presses onward, aided by his right hand man Darius. El, meanwhile, follows close behind, waiting for his chance to bring justice to the king.
name: Vol. III

description:
The Ark

With Issue 5 we follow the inhabitants of the Ark as they deal with the trials and tribulations of living on a floating fortress.

Parker interrogates the mercenary, Snare.

Gabe trains his new protege, and Gracie meanwhile goes looking for her missing companion Teddy.

The foundation is set for what will an explosive, action packed Issue 6!
name: The Ark

description:
Jesus takes the fight directly to Zeus and Isis, the two mythological gods leading a horde of desperate, worship-hungry deities! But do Jesus, Satan, and Sister Maria actually stand a chance? And can they keep their sh*t together long enough to stop the coming madness?

Note: This comic book was not actually funded via Kickstarter, nonetheless this issue is associated with the concept as Isis and Zeus are trying to fund and "kickstart" the apocalypse.

Back-up Feature:

  • Holy F*ck Origins: 1532 AD

description: Among the cultural figures of the Old West, Frederick Remington stands head and shoulders above the rest literally. A good-natured ogre by size and appetite, the artist portrays the West with such skill that the American government entrusts his safety to Lucky Luke. Looking after such a national treasure is not usually an easy task, but Luke will soon discover that Remington hardly needs protecting except maybe from his own excessive impulses...
name: The Painter

description: It's nineteenth century China and Aten Ra meets up with Sir Richard Dashing, the most decorated hero of the Victorian Age...who's also a an unrepentant womanizer, dedicated cheat and major league coward. Both Aten Ra and Dashing have to deal with the powerful and mysterious Group of Seven and the Chinese doctor who dominates the scene. Thrills, romance, laughs...a rollocking good time for all!

Six months after discovering the ability to steal any song ever written, you'd think Dave Tobin would be swimming in royalty checks, but he's back slumming it with his old band Jenny Jump! They're getting real well known around town, but recording with obsessive producer Jasper Butler is bringing them down.
name: Volume 2

description: Mapped to Jospeh Campbell's Hero Cycle, Shon C. Bury's Nox is a self-aware low fantasy populated equally by mystical gurus, Everyman characters, and dark forces bent on tipping our mundane world into shadows. Nox is as influenced by Robert Graves' White Goddess and Jeremy Narby's Cosmic Serpent as Joseph Campell's The Hero With a Thousand Faces. Come join us on this epic road trip to end all epic road trips.

Drawn by strange cries coming from the necropolis at the foot of the pyramids, Papyrus comes face to face with Anubis, the god of the dead. The jackal-headed god, angered by a rash of grave robbing, orders the young Egyptian to enter the Great Pyramid and retrieve there the heart scarab of Kheops. But the pyramid is already 1000 years old to Papyrus, and robbers have long ago desecrated it. The young boy will have to search it from top to bottom.
name: The Amulet of the Great Pyramid

description:
Time is up for Nick Morgan, Carl Sagan, and The Futurists when Major Mackenzie Cartwright and The Ascendancy arrive outside the Kepler Space Station. Their goal: Capture the Rapture Device! Meanwhile, on the imperial Earth of Alpha One, Nicholas and Tobias Morgan await execution! Can Nick reach them in time?

Note: The digital edition (2/4/2015) for this issue was released before the print edition.

Confounded at every turn, Smitty finds himself two steps behind Burroughs as their old rivalry reaches new heights of mutual hatred. As his options for survival and freedom dwindle, he'll have to learn to think like his greatest rival-and come to grips with how similar the two of them are.

Note: The digital edition (2/4/2015) for this issue was released before the print edition.

After the events of issue 2, Adrienne awakens alone on the beach without her armor. Where has Raven gone and what is she after anyway? Also, PIRATE FIGHT! The Eisner-Award nominated PRINCELESS continues!

Note: The digital edition (2/4/2015) for this issue was released before the print edition.

Rusty needles and chicken bones

When Cole is finally released from the hospital, he discovers his apartment has been tossed, but oddly, nothing is missing. His partner, Agent Alicia Reece has a theory of why he tried to kill himself that involves his friend Tommy and his past lover Jasmine, but Cole is still in denial. Through a series of mysterious forensic clues, strange dreams and weird blackouts, Cole begins to assemble the pieces of a puzzle.

Hardball

Bullets and blood fly as Trane and Allumette battle their way through heavily armed thugs at the Hardball Lounge. Plus, mercenary king Maxwell Lanois gets a visit from a deadly assassin out for revenge.
name: Hardball

description:
Ruth & Freddy must find a way to put a stop to the zombie apocalypse, rescue their grandson, survive an epic "good vs. evil" battle in the Netherworld, and ensure the goddesses Ishtar and Ereshkigal don't destroy existence as we know it - all in time to get home for Jeopardy.

The Huntress

Myth. Magic. Mayhem. The adventure continues as the powerful sorceress and talent agent C seeks her missing client among the realms. What's a badass gal to do when she can't find her quarry in Hades? Take to the savannah to enlist the aid the Queen of the Hunt, her Aunt Artemis, that's what! C just better to remember to watch out for anything that might be hunting her...
name: The Huntress

description:
Chpater 7 part 1

Danny is accidentally bitten by Brad and the group prepare for a way to undo it.
name: Chapter 7 Part 1

description: Ollie and Astrina's courtship continues as Scath, first knight of Ba, ruler of the Realm of Nightmares, searches the Plain of Imaginings for Ollie. So does a mysterious guardian known as the Grey Knight. Both are important people from Ollie's past who seem to know about a tragedy Ollie tried and failed to prevent years ago. But fate may prevent any of these mysteries from being solved when Ollie is seriously wounded defending Donnelly against another monster's attack. From award winning comic artists and writers Barb Jacobs and Steven Philip Jones comes the collected fantasy webcomic for all ages to enjoy.

As her enemies converge on her, Ada must make a difficult decision to give the curse to her closest ally in order to save his life and the life of her son. But when the truth behind her acquisition of the curse is revealed, can anyone near her be trusted?

The Runaway

In a city fractured by the chemically created undead, one girl crosses the path of the one man who can bring some sense and order into her world. Anyone with some sense would leave this place and never come back, but her brother has other ambitions and a personal army of undead slaves to help make it all happen.
name: Book Two: The Runaway

description: 1950's private detective Velda accepts an invitation to a dude ranch...and an invitation to treachery, extortion, kidnaping and molybdenum! Also in this issue: "Murder on a Shoestring" pits Velda against a crazed strangler while she has to "Play Chicken" for a larcenous hypnotist. As a bonus an adventure of Neolithica: Girl of the Pleistocene and Hawkshaw Hawk: Bird Detective round out the issue.

Close-Up

The time has come for Yota to choose between Moemi and Ai, but will either of them accept his decision? And could Yota's focus on his children's book project prevent him from truly winning the affections of the girl he adores? Meanwhile, in an effort to save Ai from being erased, the old clerk of Gokuraku Video has gone over the head of Ai's creator to a higher authority...but there's no guarantee that this powerful bearded man will be sympathetic to Ai's plight!
name: Close-Up

description:
76 pages of mutants and motormouths!

A new story begins: 'Hunting Season!' Wolverine discovers an alien weapon that turns normal people into ruthless killers! By Paul Cornell and Alan Davis!

The climax of 'The Hellfire Saga' is here as the X-Men attack the Hellfire Academy! By Jason Aaron and Nick Bradshaw!

Deadpool tackles Daredevil and the demon called Vetis! By Brian Posehn, Gerry Duggan and Mike Hawthorne!

Featuring material first printed in Wolverine and the X-Men #35, Wolverine #1-2 and Deadpool #11.

XIII is hiding in France at the Prseaus, after a past more nebulous he even believed possible caught up to him again. But the organisation thats after him hasnt said its last word, and has considerable means at its disposal. It lures Jones, on duty in Afghanistan, into a terrible ambush, for the sole purpose of serving as bait for the amnesiac who immediately rushes to her rescue. Meanwhile, Betty Barnowsky-Prseau is off to Maine to dig into XIIIs past
name: The Bait

description: In the near future, everyone is desensitized, masked men control the world, and only two unusual people can discover why no one really seems to notice. Antioch is a new series from Eisner nominee Kevin Colden (Fishtown, I Rule the Night). This color edition is digital exclusive.

Riverdale High is proof that Cupids arrow will sometimes strike in the least likely of places! There are some pretty weird pairings that have happened over the years, and were sharing them with you in this digital exclusive. Jugheads on a date?! Veronica and Cheryl are dating a couple of nerds?! Midge is going out with someone other than Moose (and hes letting it happen)?!?! These pairings are just TOO weirddont miss this!

In the year 2010, one girl arrived at the creative challenge of her life--art school. Four years and hundreds of comic pages later, her progress is collected and documented in this part-anthology, part-memoir, part-pep talk volume. Genres range from slapstick comedy to murder mysteries. There's something for everyone!

*This collects issues 1A, 1B and 1C*

The definitive version of James A. Bretney's gripping story of Mack - a dual Iraq War veteran. What is the true cost that one man pays when he goes to war?
name: TPB

description:
Antonio is a former soldier from the Brazilian Army, retired for going partialy blind and because of a heart condition. He once was in the Coluna Prestes and was responsible for hunting "cangaceiros" in the Northeast of Brazil.

He was living in a farm in the frontier of a small town with his wife and his daughter but his fate was cruel. Coronel Fortunato fell in love with Antnio's wife and gave him an ultimate: one night with his wife or his whole family murdered.

Antonio doesn't accept the offer and suffers with Coronel's rage. A famous cangaceiro finds him almost dead and refuses the end his life and then encourages Antonio to live his last moments with honor. The former soldier will wear his old uniform and go on a chase after the devilish man who ruined his life.

Harry decides to change jobs after being recommended by her best friend, Ben. At her new job she falls in love with the president, Matthew, at first sight. He is a very attractive man and an established architect. However, Ben's girlfriend, Cindy, is suspicious of Ben and Harry's relationship since they are so close. Their coworkers become sympathetic to Cindy and insult Harry behind her back. Matthew realizes that their relationship is negatively affecting the company and tells Harry: "In order to eliminate suspicion in the company, you're going to tell everyone that you are crazy about me." If she refuses, Matthew will fire her!
name: Vol. 1

description: Amber is working as a live-in gardener at a large estate when she is surprised to see the owners' weekend visitors arrive. Rocco...! Eighteen months ago, he assumed it was Amber who had written an expose for the press, detailing their relationship, and he broke it off without further discussion. Even though she was pregnant... And now, Rocco accuses Amber of spying on the rich to get money for herself, and advises her employer to fire her!
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: The Christmas Eve Bride/Born to Wed
